git config

$ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
$ git config --global user.email "johndoe@example.com"

To initialize git in folder

$ git init

To check status
$ git status

To stage the changes and commit the code to track
$ git add .
$ git add <filename>
$ git commit -m "<Message>"

To unstage the changes tou added
$ git reset .
$ git reset <filename>

To view the commits
$ git` log --all`
$ git log --all --graph
To make main as the default bracnch
$ git branch -M main
$ git branch // To check currnent branch
$ git branch <branch name> // To creat new branch

To rename branch
$ git branch -m <oldname> <newname> // At any Branch
$ git branch -m <newname> // Current Branch

To check how meny remote are there in the repository
$ git remote

To add a remote in a repository
$ git remote add <rmotename> <githubrepolink>

To upload the code to github
$ git push -u <remotename> <branchname>
